                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18191201-173-off976 t18191201-173-victim1733"></join>
                     </persName>
                     
                  , in a lodging-room
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18191201-173-person1734">
                  EDWARD 
                  HUTCHINGS
               <interp inst="t18191201-173-person1734" type="surname" value="HUTCHINGS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18191201-173-person1734" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18191201-173-person1734" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in Middlesex-street, Somers'-town. I let the prisoner a furnished lodging, at 6 s. a week; he was there near a quarter, I received no money of him. He said he had money coming from an estate in Scotland, and when that was sold he would pay me. He left, and I found every thing was gone, except a bedstead, two chairs, and a table - the articles stated in the indictment were taken away, which were let with the lodging.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18191201-173-person1735">
                  CHARLOTTE 
                  HUTCHINGS
               <interp inst="t18191201-173-person1735" type="surname" value="HUTCHINGS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18191201-173-person1735" type="given" value="CHARLOTTE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18191201-173-person1735" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I know all the things were in the room when the prisoner took it. I have only found the curtains and sheets.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18191201-173-person1736">
                  RICHARD 
                  INGSTON
               <interp inst="t18191201-173-person1736" type="surname" value="INGSTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18191201-173-person1736" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18191201-173-person1736" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a pawnbroker. I have a sheet and curtain, which I took in pledge from the prisoner on the 9th of July.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. Mrs. Hutchings sent me to pledge the things for her.</p>
